1
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:08,272
How do you miss something this basic?

2
00:01:08,272 --> 00:01:10,884
Even a newbie wouldn't screw that up.
Are you not nervous?

3
00:01:10,884 --> 00:01:14,554
<i>A company's order is built on rank.</i>

4
00:01:18,683 --> 00:01:21,061
<i>But</i>

5
00:01:21,775 --> 00:01:24,400
<i>their real power struggle</i>

6
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,492
<i>runs deeper</i>

7
00:01:26,492 --> 00:01:29,132
<i>and far more discreet.</i>

8
00:01:45,388 --> 00:01:49,668
<i>Is a perfectly equal relationship
even possible?</i>

9
00:01:58,098 --> 00:02:02,686
<i>The moment two people come together,
a hierarchy forms.</i>

10
00:02:04,562 --> 00:02:07,729
<i>Between friends, between lovers...</i>

11
00:02:07,729 --> 00:02:11,535
<i>there's always an imbalance of power.</i>

12
00:02:22,372 --> 00:02:24,263
<i>And everyone</i>

13
00:02:24,263 --> 00:02:28,263
<i>wants to climb just a little higher.</i>

14
00:02:29,487 --> 00:02:31,151
<i>Even if</i>

15
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:34,927
<i>it means crossing a line.</i>

16
00:02:34,927 --> 00:02:38,440
This is so good.

17
00:02:40,870 --> 00:02:42,400
What is that?

18
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:45,070
What?

19
00:02:45,070 --> 00:02:46,271
See? Something's floating.

20
00:02:46,271 --> 00:02:47,506
Where?

21
00:02:55,697 --> 00:02:59,451
You look great on camera, Director Kang.

22
00:03:08,293 --> 00:03:09,852
Are you police?

23
00:03:09,852 --> 00:03:11,545
No, I'm not.

24
00:03:13,319 --> 00:03:15,652
I'm...

25
00:03:49,417 --> 00:03:50,851
[Noh Ki Jun]

26
00:03:52,674 --> 00:03:55,094
From the headquarters audit team.

27
00:03:55,094 --> 00:03:58,132
Stop what you're doing and come talk to me,

28
00:03:58,132 --> 00:04:00,131
Director Kang.

29
00:04:02,389 --> 00:04:04,707
[Interview Room]
[Under Audit]

30
00:04:14,737 --> 00:04:19,936
I heard your audit team could
bring down anyone.

31
00:04:20,631 --> 00:04:22,274
Now you've got people flying, too?

32
00:04:22,274 --> 00:04:24,148
You're the one who's about to fall.

33
00:04:24,148 --> 00:04:26,579
- Hey!
- I'm Noh Ki Jun from Audit Team 1.

34
00:04:26,579 --> 00:04:29,302
You've got some nerve
talking to a director like that.

35
00:04:29,302 --> 00:04:32,393
Who do you think you are, cops? The NIS?

36
00:04:32,393 --> 00:04:34,970
This is illegal filming.

37
00:04:34,970 --> 00:04:40,159
I'll sue all of you for invasion of privacy.

38
00:04:41,984 --> 00:04:46,368
To catch a spy leaking core tech overseas,

39
00:04:46,368 --> 00:04:48,612
this is what it takes.

40
00:04:48,612 --> 00:04:50,636
We've got our reasons too.

41
00:04:50,636 --> 00:04:53,638
People like that love to cry privacy,

42
00:04:53,638 --> 00:04:57,551
but have zero sense of ethics.

43
00:04:59,313 --> 00:05:01,586
Hey.

44
00:05:01,586 --> 00:05:03,721
Take it down a notch.

45
00:05:03,721 --> 00:05:07,207
Even if I were an industrial spy,
it's a first offense.

46
00:05:07,207 --> 00:05:12,054
Act a little sorry, you'll get probation.

47
00:05:17,361 --> 00:05:18,631
Director Kang,

48
00:05:18,631 --> 00:05:20,212
he speaks Korean pretty well, right?

49
00:05:20,212 --> 00:05:21,695
Yeah, he's Korean-Chinese.

50
00:05:21,695 --> 00:05:24,201
Korean, sure.

51
00:05:24,201 --> 00:05:27,994
North Korean.

52
00:05:32,562 --> 00:05:35,740
This company's been funding them.

53
00:05:35,740 --> 00:05:38,660
It's disguised as foreign trade,

54
00:05:38,660 --> 00:05:42,360
but it's all run by the North.

55
00:05:46,201 --> 00:05:50,550
If espionage charges apply,

56
00:05:50,550 --> 00:05:54,396
then you're not just an industrial spy.
You're the real deal.

57
00:05:54,396 --> 00:05:57,504
Probation?

58
00:05:57,504 --> 00:06:01,133
You'll be doing time.

59
00:06:11,392 --> 00:06:16,318
[Interview Room]
[Under Audit]

60
00:06:16,318 --> 00:06:19,587
You idiots. I told you, it's not me.
Why won't you believe me?

61
00:06:19,587 --> 00:06:22,059
- Sir, please calm down.
- "Calm down?"

62
00:06:22,059 --> 00:06:24,664
- We got a report.
- A report? What report?

63
00:06:24,664 --> 00:06:26,730
It's all made up. Total setup.

64
00:06:26,730 --> 00:06:30,076
Team 3 never has a quiet day.

65
00:06:30,076 --> 00:06:31,815
What is it this time?

66
00:06:31,815 --> 00:06:34,292
A report says that general manager lied

67
00:06:34,292 --> 00:06:36,501
about being married and hit on her.

68
00:06:36,501 --> 00:06:39,505
She said there's a mole as proof.

69
00:06:39,505 --> 00:06:40,935
- What?
- Down there.

70
00:06:40,935 --> 00:06:43,025
There.

71
00:06:45,569 --> 00:06:48,892
<i>Haemoo Group. 7th in the conglomerate rankings.</i>

72
00:06:48,892 --> 00:06:50,477
[Haemoo Group]
<i>9th in revenue.</i>

73
00:06:50,477 --> 00:06:54,889
<i>This conglomerate, with 42 affiliates,
has its top department.</i>

74
00:06:54,889 --> 00:06:56,693
[Audit Office]
<i>Even within the audit office,</i>

75
00:06:56,693 --> 00:06:59,996
[Audit Team 1, 2, 3]
<i>there's a clear hierarchy.</i>

76
00:06:59,996 --> 00:07:01,853
<i>Teams 1 and 2</i>

77
00:07:01,853 --> 00:07:05,846
<i>handle major cases, like embezzlement,
breach of trust,</i>

78
00:07:05,846 --> 00:07:09,689
<i>collusion, and data leaks.</i>

79
00:07:09,689 --> 00:07:12,495
<i>As for Team 3...</i>

80
00:07:13,153 --> 00:07:16,157
- Alright, let go.
- Yeah.

81
00:07:16,157 --> 00:07:18,923
I'll show you.

82
00:07:21,065 --> 00:07:23,561
No, don't! Stop!

83
00:07:25,264 --> 00:07:27,221
Seriously...

84
00:07:27,221 --> 00:07:29,450
Look closely.

85
00:07:29,450 --> 00:07:33,604
- See it? A mole?
- Hey, don't cover it.

86
00:07:33,604 --> 00:07:38,083
<i>Yeah... they do this kind of thing.</i>

87
00:07:40,148 --> 00:07:45,569
[Episode 1: Up, Down, Up-Up, Down]

88
00:08:18,175 --> 00:08:21,164
- Good morning.
- Morning.

89
00:08:21,164 --> 00:08:23,441
Hey, Mr. Gentleman Noh Ki Jun.

90
00:08:23,441 --> 00:08:26,194
Looking sharp as always.

91
00:08:26,194 --> 00:08:29,698
Thanks. Let's have a good one.

92
00:08:47,688 --> 00:08:50,066
[Protecting core tech from industrial spies]

93
00:08:50,066 --> 00:08:52,227
[Haemoo Audit Office]

94
00:08:52,227 --> 00:08:55,197
[Noh Ki Jun, Audit Team 1]
<i>Auditing is about improving operations</i>

95
00:08:55,197 --> 00:08:58,661
<i>and adding value.</i>

96
00:08:58,661 --> 00:09:01,508
[Audit's Smile Angel]
[Noh Ki Jun, Audit Team 1]

97
00:09:05,661 --> 00:09:08,278
"Smile angel?" Since when is audit an angel?

98
00:09:08,278 --> 00:09:10,775
Hey, I didn't make that up.

99
00:09:10,775 --> 00:09:12,662
Why not? I'd be proud.

100
00:09:12,662 --> 00:09:16,012
He's the face of audit.

101
00:09:16,012 --> 00:09:18,909
Honestly, yesterday was embarrassing.

102
00:09:18,909 --> 00:09:21,040
What was that naked show?

103
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:23,101
Total chaos yesterday.

104
00:09:23,101 --> 00:09:26,865
I even dreamed about it.
The general manager's... you know.

105
00:09:26,865 --> 00:09:29,665
- Man...
- No way.

106
00:09:32,382 --> 00:09:35,480
- This is just kimbap.
- Sorry, sorry.

107
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:39,410
But why do we even handle stuff like that?
It's not exactly classy.

108
00:09:39,410 --> 00:09:41,274
If there's a report, we have to deal with it.

109
00:09:41,274 --> 00:09:43,298
That's what Team 3 is for.

110
00:09:43,298 --> 00:09:47,353
Teams 1 and 2 handle the big stuff,
and dump the rest on them.

111
00:09:47,353 --> 00:09:51,695
They stake out for attendance checks,
time bathroom breaks, even smoking breaks.

112
00:09:51,695 --> 00:09:56,411
I saw them going around
counting coffee sticks in every break room.

113
00:09:56,411 --> 00:09:58,205
Man, that's depressing.

114
00:09:58,205 --> 00:10:01,767
They say the HQ Audit can take down anyone.

115
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:04,552
- But Team 3...
- It's more like...

116
00:10:04,552 --> 00:10:07,309
they clean up bird crap.

117
00:10:07,309 --> 00:10:09,935
In short, the bird poop team.

118
00:10:11,340 --> 00:10:13,450
Don't let anyone hear that.

119
00:10:13,450 --> 00:10:15,873
Oh, it's Secretary Park.

120
00:10:23,227 --> 00:10:26,773
Good morning. Nice weather, huh?

121
00:10:27,764 --> 00:10:30,118
Yeah.

122
00:10:30,118 --> 00:10:32,021
Starting the day seeing her?

123
00:10:32,021 --> 00:10:34,792
That's a good sign, right?

124
00:10:34,792 --> 00:10:37,631
I'll head up first. Finish up and come up.

125
00:10:37,631 --> 00:10:40,125
Already?

126
00:11:00,306 --> 00:11:02,601
What's my schedule this afternoon?

127
00:11:02,601 --> 00:11:06,481
You have a meeting
with Haemoo Media executives.

128
00:11:13,861 --> 00:11:16,698
Nice tie.

129
00:11:21,380 --> 00:11:24,973
Thank you, sir. You've got great taste.

130
00:11:59,913 --> 00:12:03,012
- Hey.
- Hi.

131
00:12:17,044 --> 00:12:18,587
Oh, right.

132
00:12:18,587 --> 00:12:23,281
Everyone saw you on the company broadcast.
They're all asking who the hot guy is.

133
00:12:23,281 --> 00:12:26,634
Yeah? They'll lose it
when they see me in person.

134
00:12:26,634 --> 00:12:29,231
What are you doing after work?

135
00:12:29,231 --> 00:12:33,291
Want to grab a drink?
There's a nice wine bar nearby.

136
00:12:33,291 --> 00:12:37,164
- Where?
- It's called...

137
00:12:46,282 --> 00:12:48,080
Let's talk later, okay?

138
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:50,625
Ki Jun!

139
00:13:00,177 --> 00:13:03,347
Just a moment. Hey!

140
00:13:08,579 --> 00:13:10,760
Ji Hye.

141
00:13:12,407 --> 00:13:16,250
That's quite a greeting.

142
00:13:16,250 --> 00:13:18,794
I missed you.

143
00:13:18,794 --> 00:13:23,254
You meeting her tonight?
Hang out with me instead.

144
00:13:24,043 --> 00:13:25,579
Wait.

145
00:13:29,283 --> 00:13:31,827
Aren't you getting married?

146
00:13:31,827 --> 00:13:32,876
Called it off?

147
00:13:32,876 --> 00:13:34,818
No, but...

148
00:13:34,818 --> 00:13:36,957
I've been feeling down.

149
00:13:36,957 --> 00:13:41,950
The thought of being with one man forever...

150
00:13:43,239 --> 00:13:45,549
Can we

151
00:13:45,549 --> 00:13:49,895
have one last night?

152
00:13:55,348 --> 00:13:58,420
I'm not that kind of guy.

153
00:14:06,201 --> 00:14:10,479
Pre-wedding jitters are normal.

154
00:14:10,479 --> 00:14:12,816
I'll make it up to you

155
00:14:12,816 --> 00:14:15,945
with a generous wedding gift.

156
00:14:15,945 --> 00:14:17,630
Oh please.

157
00:14:17,630 --> 00:14:20,133
How generous?

158
00:14:26,031 --> 00:14:28,477
Wait.

159
00:14:47,116 --> 00:14:48,146
What are you doing?

160
00:14:48,146 --> 00:14:49,890
Hey, Ki Jun.

161
00:14:49,890 --> 00:14:51,327
Look, it's blooming.

162
00:14:51,327 --> 00:14:53,800
Who's been watering this thing?

163
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:56,606
Pretty impressive for this dull office.

164
00:14:56,606 --> 00:14:58,739
You're getting sentimental.

165
00:14:58,739 --> 00:15:03,274
Not like you'd care. Your life's in full bloom.

166
00:15:03,274 --> 00:15:06,151
I heard from HR just now.

167
00:15:06,151 --> 00:15:08,568
Something about a promotion
after the Director Kang case.

168
00:15:08,568 --> 00:15:09,968
That true?

169
00:15:10,977 --> 00:15:14,882
- I don't know.
- Come on. Must be true, huh?

170
00:15:14,882 --> 00:15:19,717
Executive Kim really backed you, didn't he?

171
00:15:20,835 --> 00:15:25,365
I got on your side early. Don't forget that.

172
00:15:25,365 --> 00:15:27,049
Guys!

173
00:15:27,049 --> 00:15:28,755
Did you hear?

174
00:15:28,755 --> 00:15:29,784
What?

175
00:15:29,784 --> 00:15:33,152
The whole company's on edge.
There's this scary rumor going around.

176
00:15:33,152 --> 00:15:34,826
It's serious.

177
00:15:34,826 --> 00:15:36,784
What is it?

178
00:15:37,872 --> 00:15:39,857
She's coming back,

179
00:15:39,857 --> 00:15:42,285
Joo In Ah.

180
00:15:48,037 --> 00:15:49,105
[New message received]

181
00:15:49,105 --> 00:15:50,294
[Class of '19 Group Chat]
Isn't that Joo In Ah?

182
00:15:50,294 --> 00:15:52,293
[Class of '22 Group Chat]
It's Joo In Ah.

183
00:15:52,293 --> 00:15:54,800
[I'm already stressed...]
[No way]

184
00:15:58,765 --> 00:16:00,002
<i>She's here.</i>

185
00:16:00,002 --> 00:16:02,255
<i>- We're screwed...
- Is she back for good?</i>

186
00:16:02,255 --> 00:16:04,322
<i>- Might be time to quit.
- Why'd she come back?</i>

187
00:16:04,322 --> 00:16:06,529
<i>- I'm already stressed...
- Too many CCs are the worst.</i>

188
00:16:06,529 --> 00:16:11,325
[Will this affect overseas too?]
[Even the field teams are on edge]

189
00:16:11,325 --> 00:16:13,247
Watch out

190
00:16:13,247 --> 00:16:16,073
for people with nicknames.

191
00:16:16,073 --> 00:16:20,459
They're made for easy trash talk.

192
00:16:20,459 --> 00:16:23,676
Joo In Ah probably has

193
00:16:23,676 --> 00:16:25,840
a dozen.

194
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:28,916
You know "Joo In Ah-out?"

195
00:16:28,916 --> 00:16:32,921
If she targets you, you're out.

196
00:16:32,921 --> 00:16:35,723
My favorite's this one. "Office ghost."

197
00:16:35,723 --> 00:16:40,693
She practically lives here, day and night.

198
00:16:40,693 --> 00:16:43,899
She picked up another nickname overseas.

199
00:16:43,899 --> 00:16:44,924
What is it?

200
00:16:44,924 --> 00:16:48,890
She got into it with a gang
over business rights.

201
00:16:49,888 --> 00:16:52,657
So now

202
00:16:52,657 --> 00:16:55,171
it's "Joo Sniper."

203
00:16:55,171 --> 00:16:57,275
Wait, she actually shot someone?

204
00:16:57,275 --> 00:16:58,519
Probably just a rumor.

205
00:16:58,519 --> 00:17:01,319
How does a rumor get that crazy?

206
00:17:01,319 --> 00:17:04,085
What matters is

207
00:17:04,085 --> 00:17:06,916
which team she joins.

208
00:17:06,916 --> 00:17:08,905
Right?

209
00:17:22,397 --> 00:17:26,124
[Kim Jin Hee, Planning Team:
She got on the elevator]

210
00:17:26,944 --> 00:17:30,817
- Joo In Ah just got on the elevator.
- Which floor did she press?

211
00:17:36,794 --> 00:17:38,884
He says she's smashing every button.

212
00:17:38,884 --> 00:17:43,565
Man, my heart's about to burst.

213
00:17:43,565 --> 00:17:45,945
Passed 4F.

214
00:17:47,284 --> 00:17:48,764
And 5F...

215
00:17:48,764 --> 00:17:51,902
Passed 6F!

216
00:17:53,557 --> 00:17:55,429
Where is she even going?

217
00:17:55,429 --> 00:17:57,891
- Did HR post anything?
- Not yet.

218
00:17:57,891 --> 00:17:59,789
[HR & Information Office]

219
00:18:00,560 --> 00:18:03,101
[Bu Se Yeong, Head of HR]

220
00:18:10,862 --> 00:18:12,600
[Request for HR Transfer Approval]

221
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:15,516
[Cancel] [Confirm]

222
00:18:17,517 --> 00:18:20,064
9F.

223
00:18:21,123 --> 00:18:22,895
[Please don't stop at 14...]
10F.

224
00:18:22,895 --> 00:18:25,131
[Please...]
Why does she keep coming up?

225
00:18:25,131 --> 00:18:27,156
[Just don't get off on my floor]
[Keep going, please]

226
00:18:27,156 --> 00:18:29,433
[Please get off...]
[Why is this elevator so slow today?]

227
00:18:31,383 --> 00:18:33,261
[I'm getting off first]
[Lucky you]

228
00:18:35,137 --> 00:18:37,764
[Passed 13 for now]
[Is this the stop?]

229
00:18:37,764 --> 00:18:39,347
[14F]

230
00:19:08,222 --> 00:19:11,022
14F!

231
00:19:16,928 --> 00:19:18,846
[Planning, Audit Office]

232
00:19:18,846 --> 00:19:20,431
Stay calm!

233
00:19:20,431 --> 00:19:23,934
Planning's on 14 too.

234
00:19:23,934 --> 00:19:25,448
[Planning Office]

235
00:19:25,448 --> 00:19:27,479
Hey, clean over there too!

236
00:19:27,479 --> 00:19:29,506
Hurry! Hurry!

237
00:19:29,506 --> 00:19:31,531
All that scrap paper and coffee on your desk!

238
00:19:31,531 --> 00:19:35,636
Finish it and toss it, now!

239
00:20:00,095 --> 00:20:02,179
Mr. Kim Gyu Young?

240
00:20:16,605 --> 00:20:18,029
Nice to meet you.

241
00:20:18,029 --> 00:20:21,849
I'm Joo In Ah, your new Head of Audit.

242
00:20:27,941 --> 00:20:31,305
What is this? Why's it so gloomy in here?

243
00:20:31,305 --> 00:20:33,832
Should I sing something?

244
00:20:40,084 --> 00:20:44,041
Thanks for the warm welcome.

245
00:20:44,041 --> 00:20:45,637
Nice to meet you.

246
00:20:45,637 --> 00:20:47,893
Manager Kwon Myung Jin.

247
00:20:47,893 --> 00:20:49,283
Nice to meet you.

248
00:20:49,283 --> 00:20:51,373
You look thrilled. Relax.

249
00:20:51,373 --> 00:20:52,907
Oh, sorry.

250
00:20:52,907 --> 00:20:55,464
Moon Kyung Jin, Deputy Manager, Audit Team 1.

251
00:20:55,464 --> 00:20:57,077
Deputy Manager?

252
00:20:57,077 --> 00:21:00,334
You look so young. Nice to meet you.

253
00:21:00,334 --> 00:21:03,265
Kim Tae Hwan, Team Leader of Audit Team 2.
Nice to meet you.

254
00:21:03,265 --> 00:21:06,360
I should be saying that. Thank you.

255
00:21:06,360 --> 00:21:09,039
Jung Dong Min, Deputy Manager, Team 2.

256
00:21:09,039 --> 00:21:10,620
Nice to meet you.

257
00:21:10,620 --> 00:21:13,877
Joo Yeon Woo, Senior Staff of Team 1.

258
00:21:13,877 --> 00:21:17,800
We share the same last name.

259
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:21,726
- It's a pretty great one.
- That's right.

260
00:21:22,428 --> 00:21:24,179
Nice to meet you.

261
00:21:24,179 --> 00:21:26,557
She's more normal than I thought.

262
00:21:26,557 --> 00:21:28,370
Guess the rumors weren't true.

263
00:21:28,370 --> 00:21:32,309
Yeah, I got worked up for nothing.

264
00:21:32,309 --> 00:21:35,693
Hello, I'm Sung Doo Gi, Senior Staff of Team 1.

265
00:21:35,693 --> 00:21:36,848
Nice to meet you.

266
00:21:36,848 --> 00:21:38,318
I like the energy.

267
00:21:38,318 --> 00:21:39,383
Keep it up.

268
00:21:39,383 --> 00:21:40,432
Thank you.

269
00:21:40,432 --> 00:21:44,284
Ahn Min Soo, Assistant Manager, same team.
Go easy on me.

270
00:21:44,284 --> 00:21:46,187
I'll expect you to be charming.

271
00:21:46,187 --> 00:21:48,131
Yes.

272
00:21:50,620 --> 00:21:53,697
Hello, I'm Noh Ki Jun,
Assistant Manager, Team 1.

273
00:21:55,833 --> 00:21:58,288
Assistant Manager Noh Ki Jun?

274
00:22:13,583 --> 00:22:15,718
Let's get to work.

275
00:22:24,520 --> 00:22:25,851
Excuse me.

276
00:22:25,851 --> 00:22:27,951
Could you take a look?

277
00:22:27,951 --> 00:22:30,832
No problem. Let me see.

278
00:22:35,721 --> 00:22:40,899
It's the routine audit notice.
Needs your approval right away.

279
00:22:40,899 --> 00:22:42,436
Haemoo Industries.

280
00:22:42,436 --> 00:22:43,962
Five years in a row?

281
00:22:43,962 --> 00:22:45,556
Yeah, right.

282
00:22:45,556 --> 00:22:49,318
I've handled it ever since
I transferred here from Haemoo Industries.

283
00:22:49,318 --> 00:22:52,963
So you've been auditing your old team
for five years.

284
00:22:52,963 --> 00:22:53,982
[Routine Audit Notice]

285
00:22:54,577 --> 00:22:58,127
That's enough. Time to move on.

286
00:22:58,127 --> 00:23:01,871
Same affiliate, two years max.
That's the rule now.

287
00:23:01,871 --> 00:23:05,024
One year for former teams.

288
00:23:07,561 --> 00:23:11,854
I get what you're saying,

289
00:23:11,854 --> 00:23:15,058
but I know that place best.

290
00:23:15,058 --> 00:23:18,979
I know exactly where the problems are.

291
00:23:18,979 --> 00:23:23,595
How rotten is it
that you couldn't dig it up in five years?

292
00:23:28,025 --> 00:23:29,976
Oh, come on.

293
00:23:29,976 --> 00:23:33,229
- It's just...
- You smiling?

294
00:23:43,878 --> 00:23:46,576
If I say don't go,

295
00:23:46,576 --> 00:23:49,107
then don't go.

296
00:23:49,107 --> 00:23:50,915
Why nitpick every little thing?

297
00:23:50,915 --> 00:23:55,135
You think I'm here to debate you?

298
00:23:55,135 --> 00:23:57,938
If you knew that place so well,

299
00:23:57,938 --> 00:24:00,245
why'd you just skim the surface?

300
00:24:00,245 --> 00:24:03,262
Not a single major disciplinary case.

301
00:24:03,262 --> 00:24:07,415
Hard to go after your old buddies?

302
00:24:07,415 --> 00:24:09,303
No, that's not it.

303
00:24:09,303 --> 00:24:12,943
Or were you in on it?
Got something tucked away?

304
00:24:12,943 --> 00:24:14,487
Should I dig into it?

305
00:24:14,487 --> 00:24:17,086
Were you auditing or doing business?

306
00:24:17,086 --> 00:24:18,812
How could you say that...

307
00:24:18,812 --> 00:24:20,743
Then what is it?

308
00:24:20,743 --> 00:24:24,067
You just don't respect your new boss, huh?

309
00:24:24,067 --> 00:24:27,322
I'm sorry.

310
00:24:40,917 --> 00:24:43,755
Guess no one's that busy.

311
00:24:47,714 --> 00:24:49,105
So...

312
00:24:49,105 --> 00:24:51,655
we'll start one-on-ones now.

313
00:24:51,655 --> 00:24:55,421
When I call your name, come in.

314
00:25:03,361 --> 00:25:05,534
[Cost of opening a chicken shop]

315
00:25:05,534 --> 00:25:08,043
[Should I quit...]

316
00:25:08,043 --> 00:25:10,465
[I want to cry]

317
00:25:10,465 --> 00:25:12,837
[Interview Room]

318
00:25:23,085 --> 00:25:26,131
Manager Ha Jin Woo, Team 2.

319
00:25:35,228 --> 00:25:39,115
This place turned into Jurassic Park fast.

320
00:25:39,115 --> 00:25:41,011
Hey, can you even work like this?

321
00:25:41,011 --> 00:25:42,052
Well...

322
00:25:42,052 --> 00:25:44,629
She didn't say anything wrong.

323
00:25:44,629 --> 00:25:46,653
Guess high performers think alike.

324
00:25:46,653 --> 00:25:49,207
Heard she got promoted three times too.

325
00:25:50,646 --> 00:25:54,013
Hey, you heading to Haemoo Pharma again?

326
00:25:54,013 --> 00:25:56,097
What is it this time?

327
00:25:56,097 --> 00:25:59,556
Something shady over there?

328
00:25:59,556 --> 00:26:05,206
I'll tell you when it's ready.

329
00:26:05,206 --> 00:26:09,280
Man, you promotion junkies...

330
00:26:17,597 --> 00:26:19,683
Please get him a glass of water.

331
00:26:19,683 --> 00:26:21,117
Yes.

332
00:26:23,485 --> 00:26:26,172
I'm screwed.

333
00:26:36,162 --> 00:26:38,723
Assistant Manager Noh Ki Jun, Team 1.

334
00:26:39,956 --> 00:26:41,590
Yes.

335
00:26:47,286 --> 00:26:50,216
Each interview will be capped at three minutes.

336
00:26:50,216 --> 00:26:54,368
Yes, I'm all for efficient meetings.

337
00:26:54,368 --> 00:26:57,219
Alright, Assistant Manager Noh Ki Jun.

338
00:26:57,219 --> 00:26:59,181
[Performance Evaluation Sheet]
Excellent reviews.

339
00:26:59,181 --> 00:27:01,987
Straight S ratings since you joined.

340
00:27:01,987 --> 00:27:03,065
I've been lucky.

341
00:27:03,065 --> 00:27:05,350
So it was luck.

342
00:27:07,841 --> 00:27:11,687
You've handled major cases
across key affiliates.

343
00:27:11,687 --> 00:27:13,811
Quite a track record.

344
00:27:13,811 --> 00:27:15,835
I worked hard

345
00:27:15,835 --> 00:27:18,116
to make that luck happen.

346
00:27:18,116 --> 00:27:21,796
Okay. Let's adjust your position.

347
00:27:21,796 --> 00:27:23,621
<i>A promotion?</i>

348
00:27:23,621 --> 00:27:25,266
<i>Already?</i>

349
00:27:25,266 --> 00:27:28,943
- But it's not review season yet.
- Doesn't matter.

350
00:27:28,943 --> 00:27:31,387
If that's your call, I appreciate...

351
00:27:31,387 --> 00:27:33,577
You're moving to Team 3.

352
00:27:33,577 --> 00:27:34,837
Sorry? Team 3?

353
00:27:34,837 --> 00:27:37,881
You'll handle PM cases there.

354
00:27:37,881 --> 00:27:39,221
PM in Audit means...

355
00:27:39,221 --> 00:27:40,425
"Public Morals."

356
00:27:40,425 --> 00:27:42,629
"P" from Public, "M" from Morals.

357
00:27:42,629 --> 00:27:45,452
Mostly office affairs.

358
00:27:45,452 --> 00:27:48,489
You want me handling affairs?

359
00:27:48,489 --> 00:27:50,209
Yes.

360
00:27:52,682 --> 00:27:54,233
So...

361
00:27:54,233 --> 00:27:57,433
You start today.

362
00:28:04,373 --> 00:28:05,650
Excuse me.

363
00:28:05,650 --> 00:28:07,847
Why am I being assigned to PM in Team 3?

364
00:28:07,847 --> 00:28:09,870
I just don't get it.

365
00:28:09,870 --> 00:28:11,980
Why should I have to convince you?

366
00:28:11,980 --> 00:28:14,400
- I'm exercising my authority.
- Right.

367
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:17,500
But you said it yourself.
My evaluations are all strong.

368
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:22,017
Good job.

369
00:28:23,444 --> 00:28:24,942
Our team?

370
00:28:24,942 --> 00:28:26,876
I was going to tell you later, but

371
00:28:26,876 --> 00:28:31,736
there's an Audit I've been leading in Team 1.
A key affiliate case.

372
00:28:31,736 --> 00:28:33,180
Let me finish it.

373
00:28:33,180 --> 00:28:35,273
Upload everything to the team cloud.

374
00:28:35,273 --> 00:28:37,650
I'll review and reassign it.

375
00:28:37,650 --> 00:28:40,427
The logic's complex,
and it involves key personnel.

376
00:28:40,427 --> 00:28:44,079
It needs a subtle approach.

377
00:28:44,079 --> 00:28:47,026
The person who can close this?

378
00:28:48,006 --> 00:28:50,939
That's me.

379
00:29:09,535 --> 00:29:11,721
That's funny.

380
00:29:13,322 --> 00:29:14,536
Hey.

381
00:29:14,536 --> 00:29:17,242
What makes you so special? Got superpowers?

382
00:29:17,242 --> 00:29:18,885
Can you fly? Teleport?

383
00:29:18,885 --> 00:29:20,792
Shoot energy blasts?

384
00:29:20,792 --> 00:29:26,386
Who do you think you are?
You really believe only you can do this job?

385
00:29:26,386 --> 00:29:27,941
Don't tell me

386
00:29:27,941 --> 00:29:31,218
you think you're irreplaceable.

387
00:29:31,218 --> 00:29:33,668
Phones sell just fine without Steve Jobs.

388
00:29:33,668 --> 00:29:37,857
You think Haemoo Audit Team 1
stops without you?

389
00:29:38,529 --> 00:29:41,126
How can you be this naive?

390
00:29:41,126 --> 00:29:43,066
Fine, think what you want.

391
00:29:43,066 --> 00:29:46,990
But saying it to my face?

392
00:29:46,990 --> 00:29:49,576
That's bold.

393
00:29:51,781 --> 00:29:56,568
I'll let it slide this time.
Don't waste my time again.

394
00:29:58,335 --> 00:30:01,472
At least tell me why.

395
00:30:01,472 --> 00:30:06,280
There must be a reason you picked me for PM.

396
00:30:06,280 --> 00:30:10,146
Because you're...

397
00:30:11,679 --> 00:30:13,895
perfect for it.

398
00:30:21,645 --> 00:30:23,782
Hey, what happened?

399
00:30:23,782 --> 00:30:25,632
I thought you were getting promoted.

400
00:30:25,632 --> 00:30:29,553
Promotion? This is a demotion.

401
00:30:29,553 --> 00:30:32,492
Team 3, and PM?

402
00:30:32,492 --> 00:30:35,657
But they're nice people.

403
00:30:35,657 --> 00:30:40,409
Right, yeah. They seem really nice.

404
00:30:40,409 --> 00:30:43,095
Just help them out.

405
00:30:45,294 --> 00:30:48,051
Help them out. They seem nice.

406
00:30:48,051 --> 00:30:50,324
Do your best.

407
00:30:55,003 --> 00:30:58,831
It's Audit's ace, Assistant Manager Noh Ki Jun!

408
00:30:58,831 --> 00:31:00,143
Welcome.

409
00:31:00,143 --> 00:31:02,213
How old are you again?

410
00:31:02,213 --> 00:31:04,567
Not married yet, right? Or couldn't?

411
00:31:04,567 --> 00:31:06,677
<i>Team Leader Moo Gwang Il,</i>

412
00:31:06,677 --> 00:31:08,004
<i>Audit's official "gave up on promotion."</i>

413
00:31:08,004 --> 00:31:10,834
[Too much talker / Married]
You know, being single's the trend these days.

414
00:31:10,834 --> 00:31:15,010
Think of it as a welcome kit.
Go ahead, check it.

415
00:31:15,010 --> 00:31:17,995
<i>Pyeon Hae Young, the team's backbone
who runs the office.</i>

416
00:31:17,995 --> 00:31:19,337
[Strict at work / Single]

417
00:31:19,337 --> 00:31:21,440
Everything you need should be in there.

418
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:25,840
It's usually two pens, but I added one more.

419
00:31:25,840 --> 00:31:30,957
If you need more,
write your name, sign, and take it.

420
00:31:30,957 --> 00:31:33,647
For a big company like Haemoo,
this feels a bit cheap.

421
00:31:33,647 --> 00:31:37,892
Take it up with him.

422
00:31:37,892 --> 00:31:41,535
All I did was grab a battery once.
She's too much.

423
00:31:41,535 --> 00:31:43,985
You took the whole pack.

424
00:31:43,985 --> 00:31:47,838
AA and AAA, two packs.

425
00:31:47,838 --> 00:31:51,476
<i>Manager Cha Seong Tae,
always looking for something to pocket.</i>

426
00:31:51,476 --> 00:31:53,573
[Meju Market rating 78.8° / Married]
Seriously...

427
00:31:53,573 --> 00:31:54,698
Excuse me, sir.

428
00:31:54,698 --> 00:31:57,099
Welcome to Team 3.

429
00:31:57,099 --> 00:32:00,736
If you need anything, just let me know anytime.

430
00:32:00,736 --> 00:32:02,880
<i>Baek Hyun Gyu, the self-appointed fixer.</i>

431
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:04,639
[Grateful for audit work / Single]
<i>They call him White Blood Cell.</i>

432
00:32:04,639 --> 00:32:09,275
Let me adjust your chair before you sit.

433
00:32:18,260 --> 00:32:19,431
<i>Wait,</i>

434
00:32:19,431 --> 00:32:21,736
[Can't hear you / Single]
<i>wasn't Yoon Da Ye here?</i>

435
00:32:21,736 --> 00:32:26,463
<i>Seoul National, CPA, insane resume.</i>

436
00:32:26,463 --> 00:32:29,897
Hello, Assistant Manager Yoon.

437
00:32:29,897 --> 00:32:32,074
She's MZ.

438
00:32:32,074 --> 00:32:35,087
You know, MZ?

439
00:32:41,470 --> 00:32:46,081
<i>How is this team supposed to work?</i>

440
00:32:46,081 --> 00:32:48,700
<i>Damn it.</i>

441
00:32:48,700 --> 00:32:50,545
<i>I can't believe...</i>

442
00:32:50,545 --> 00:32:52,442
<i>I can't believe</i>

443
00:32:52,442 --> 00:32:56,501
<i>I'm stuck with them.</i>

444
00:33:20,532 --> 00:33:23,938
Already time for him to get off work.

445
00:33:27,072 --> 00:33:30,092
Is he late again?

446
00:33:32,284 --> 00:33:33,840
[Honey]

447
00:33:40,598 --> 00:33:45,710
<i>Your call can't be completed.
You'll be charged after the beep.</i>

448
00:33:56,650 --> 00:33:57,973
Yes.

449
00:33:57,973 --> 00:34:00,130
Got it.

450
00:34:00,130 --> 00:34:02,108
- What did they say?
- Spoke to the vendor.

451
00:34:02,108 --> 00:34:03,972
They'll meet the deadline.

452
00:34:03,972 --> 00:34:05,384
Nice, well done.

453
00:34:05,384 --> 00:34:07,528
You're really good at this.

454
00:34:07,528 --> 00:34:10,072
Learned from the best.

455
00:34:10,072 --> 00:34:12,217
Hey, your phone's ringing.

456
00:34:15,064 --> 00:34:17,228
Hey, honey.

457
00:34:17,228 --> 00:34:20,868
Did I not tell you? We've got a team dinner.

458
00:34:21,527 --> 00:34:23,371
Another one?

459
00:34:23,371 --> 00:34:24,940
Yeah, sorry. It's been hectic.

460
00:34:24,940 --> 00:34:26,688
Hello, ma'am.

461
00:34:26,688 --> 00:34:29,305
This is Deputy Manager Jung Mi Yeong.

462
00:34:29,305 --> 00:34:31,485
Oh, hello.

463
00:34:31,485 --> 00:34:35,262
Hard to see your husband these days, right?
The TF's been intense.

464
00:34:35,262 --> 00:34:39,949
I'll try to send him home early.

465
00:34:39,949 --> 00:34:42,335
I'll be home early. Sorry.

466
00:34:42,335 --> 00:34:45,414
Okay. Don't be too late.

467
00:34:59,473 --> 00:35:04,353
Who does she think she is,
sending my husband home?

468
00:35:10,591 --> 00:35:13,670
Who does she think she is?

469
00:35:19,224 --> 00:35:22,370
Damn it!

470
00:35:25,803 --> 00:35:27,273
So...

471
00:35:27,273 --> 00:35:29,780
this is the hotline desk.

472
00:35:29,780 --> 00:35:34,516
We get a lot of tips. Just answer and log them.

473
00:35:36,086 --> 00:35:37,255
Got it.

474
00:35:37,255 --> 00:35:38,806
Yeah.

475
00:35:48,436 --> 00:35:50,973
Hello, Audit Team 1...

476
00:35:50,973 --> 00:35:52,456
No, I mean Team 3.

477
00:35:52,456 --> 00:35:53,893
<i>Hello.</i>

478
00:35:53,893 --> 00:35:56,276
<i>This is a bit awkward, but...</i>

479
00:35:56,276 --> 00:36:00,136
<i>It's about our team leader.</i>

480
00:36:00,136 --> 00:36:01,833
Yes.

481
00:36:01,833 --> 00:36:04,126
Are you reporting an internal issue?

482
00:36:04,126 --> 00:36:07,683
<i>He keeps farting in the office.</i>

483
00:36:07,683 --> 00:36:09,167
<i>It's really bad.</i>

484
00:36:09,167 --> 00:36:12,213
<i>All day, nonstop. The air's unbearable.</i>

485
00:36:12,213 --> 00:36:15,979
<i>At least get us an air purifier.</i>

486
00:36:18,196 --> 00:36:21,176
Oh, I see.

487
00:36:33,610 --> 00:36:35,386
Hello, this is...

488
00:36:35,386 --> 00:36:38,703
<i>Hey, you bastard! Why'd you pick up so late?</i>

489
00:36:38,703 --> 00:36:41,433
<i>You get paid for this, don't you? Shit.</i>

490
00:36:41,433 --> 00:36:43,403
- This is Audit.
<i>- What?</i>

491
00:36:43,403 --> 00:36:47,216
<i>Your company needs to crash for you to wake up.</i>

492
00:36:47,216 --> 00:36:49,106
Yeah.

493
00:36:49,106 --> 00:36:50,853
- What would you like to report?
<i>- Report?</i>

494
00:36:50,853 --> 00:36:53,183
<i>I'm reporting your life, you idiot.
What's your name?</i>

495
00:36:53,183 --> 00:36:55,876
<i>I'll tell your chairman myself.</i>

496
00:36:55,876 --> 00:37:00,056
<i>What's your name? Damn it!</i>

497
00:37:03,912 --> 00:37:05,536
What is this?

498
00:37:05,536 --> 00:37:07,606
It's proof of an affair.

499
00:37:07,606 --> 00:37:11,199
I dug it out of the trash.

500
00:37:11,199 --> 00:37:14,092
So what is this...

501
00:37:21,135 --> 00:37:24,182
Hey, where are you going?

502
00:38:02,908 --> 00:38:05,567
Ki Jun, you okay?

503
00:38:05,567 --> 00:38:08,681
You looked pale going in.

504
00:38:08,681 --> 00:38:10,998
Want someone to pat your back?

505
00:38:10,998 --> 00:38:14,293
Or should I come in?

506
00:38:24,140 --> 00:38:26,153
I'm fine.

507
00:38:28,007 --> 00:38:30,304
You sure?

508
00:38:30,304 --> 00:38:33,668
If it's too much, take a break.

509
00:38:33,668 --> 00:38:37,161
You know, health comes first.

510
00:38:48,124 --> 00:38:50,975
Let's make the formal introductions.

511
00:38:50,975 --> 00:38:54,251
This is Joo In Ah, our new Head of Audit.

512
00:38:55,096 --> 00:38:59,352
And Executive Kim Han Soo,
former Head of Audit, now Head of Strategy.

513
00:38:59,352 --> 00:39:01,532
I've heard a lot about you.

514
00:39:01,532 --> 00:39:04,165
Congratulations on the promotion.

515
00:39:04,165 --> 00:39:06,408
Head of HR, Bu Se Yeong.

516
00:39:06,408 --> 00:39:09,056
In Ah, long time.

517
00:39:09,872 --> 00:39:13,484
We used to be on the same team.

518
00:39:13,484 --> 00:39:17,136
I was her senior.

519
00:39:17,136 --> 00:39:18,873
Se Yeong.

520
00:39:18,873 --> 00:39:20,897
You look great.

521
00:39:20,897 --> 00:39:22,861
HR must suit you.

522
00:39:25,944 --> 00:39:30,465
You two seem close. Great to see.

523
00:39:30,465 --> 00:39:34,858
This appointment was a brilliant move.

524
00:39:34,858 --> 00:39:38,275
Audit is the company's blade,

525
00:39:38,275 --> 00:39:41,875
serving the Vice Chairman and the Chairman.

526
00:39:41,875 --> 00:39:45,332
Someone like you fits perfectly.

527
00:39:45,332 --> 00:39:48,281
Oh, you knew it.

528
00:39:49,516 --> 00:39:51,673
I'm pretty good with a blade.

529
00:39:54,205 --> 00:39:57,021
Yeah, she has a sharp wit.

530
00:39:57,021 --> 00:39:59,548
You guys will get used to it.

531
00:40:01,098 --> 00:40:03,130
How does it feel to be back in Seoul?

532
00:40:03,130 --> 00:40:05,322
Air's the same everywhere.

533
00:40:06,005 --> 00:40:08,992
Maybe a bit more polluted here.

534
00:40:08,992 --> 00:40:10,603
So...

535
00:40:11,765 --> 00:40:14,845
Any regrets about coming back?

536
00:40:22,400 --> 00:40:24,275
If I did,

537
00:40:24,275 --> 00:40:27,961
could I go back?

538
00:40:44,297 --> 00:40:46,169
Time flies.

539
00:40:46,169 --> 00:40:47,929
Shall we get dinner?

540
00:40:47,929 --> 00:40:50,888
I still have a lot to review.

541
00:40:50,888 --> 00:40:52,706
Rain check.

542
00:40:52,706 --> 00:40:54,066
Next time, let's grab some steak.

543
00:40:54,066 --> 00:40:55,760
Of course.

544
00:40:57,029 --> 00:40:58,666
What about you, Vice Chairman?

545
00:40:58,666 --> 00:41:00,900
I'm having dinner at home tonight.

546
00:41:00,900 --> 00:41:02,973
My wife's probably already there.

547
00:41:02,973 --> 00:41:04,891
See?

548
00:41:04,891 --> 00:41:08,070
He's a total family man.

549
00:41:08,070 --> 00:41:10,801
How's the Chairman doing?

550
00:41:10,801 --> 00:41:14,411
He was discharged last week.
We're keeping an eye on him.

551
00:41:15,770 --> 00:41:19,043
I check on him regularly.

552
00:42:15,849 --> 00:42:18,799
<i>Your call can't be completed.</i>

553
00:42:26,057 --> 00:42:28,881
<i>Your call can't be completed.</i>

554
00:42:34,195 --> 00:42:36,477
<i>Why aren't you answering?</i>

555
00:42:36,477 --> 00:42:38,727
<i>Call me. Why won't you pick up?</i>

556
00:42:38,727 --> 00:42:40,663
<i>Call me. Still at the dinner?</i>

557
00:42:40,663 --> 00:42:42,876
<i>When are you coming home?</i>

558
00:42:48,754 --> 00:42:50,369
It sucks.

559
00:42:58,864 --> 00:43:00,782
Alright, our dream team,

560
00:43:00,782 --> 00:43:03,688
Deputy Manager Son

561
00:43:03,688 --> 00:43:06,049
and Deputy Manager Jung.

562
00:43:08,354 --> 00:43:12,081
This brand launch is
make-or-break for Haemoo Food Division.

563
00:43:12,081 --> 00:43:12,949
Yeah.

564
00:43:12,949 --> 00:43:15,475
You two need to create maximum synergy.

565
00:43:15,475 --> 00:43:17,305
- Yes, sir.
- We'll do our best.

566
00:43:17,305 --> 00:43:18,932
- You sure?
- We'll give it our all.

567
00:43:18,932 --> 00:43:20,470
Alright, cheers.

568
00:43:20,470 --> 00:43:22,157
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

569
00:43:22,157 --> 00:43:24,815
- Let's go for it.
- Let's do it.

570
00:43:30,661 --> 00:43:33,661
- You drank yesterday too?
- Yeah...

571
00:43:44,093 --> 00:43:49,420
<i>Your call can't be completed.
You'll be charged after the beep.</i>

572
00:44:09,794 --> 00:44:11,723
Honey!

573
00:44:15,551 --> 00:44:17,473
Sorry.

574
00:44:35,501 --> 00:44:37,884
<i>Your call can't be completed...</i>

575
00:45:23,182 --> 00:45:24,799
Damn it! Open the door!

576
00:45:24,799 --> 00:45:27,113
Hey, open up!

577
00:45:27,113 --> 00:45:28,898
Open it or I'll kill you!

578
00:45:28,898 --> 00:45:30,582
Open the door!

579
00:45:30,582 --> 00:45:32,834
- Hey!
- Honey?

580
00:45:35,764 --> 00:45:37,702
What are you doing?

581
00:46:04,563 --> 00:46:06,226
Heading out already?

582
00:46:10,520 --> 00:46:13,197
Why does he look so out of it?

583
00:46:13,197 --> 00:46:15,913
He has changed in half a day.

584
00:46:50,749 --> 00:46:53,098
[Waiting anxiously for the results]

585
00:46:53,098 --> 00:46:56,964
[Jung Sang Hyun]
[2-star to 1-star demotion]

586
00:46:58,284 --> 00:47:02,832
<i>The verse lacked precision...</i>

587
00:47:04,011 --> 00:47:07,832
<i>There's no such thing as a permanent hierarchy.</i>

588
00:47:09,014 --> 00:47:10,825
<i>That's why</i>

589
00:47:12,004 --> 00:47:14,381
<i>the higher you go,</i>

590
00:47:14,381 --> 00:47:16,403
<i>the more anxious you get.</i>

591
00:47:42,426 --> 00:47:44,091
This is so embarrassing.

592
00:47:44,091 --> 00:47:46,536
How did you even find the place?

593
00:47:46,536 --> 00:47:48,801
Did you go around checking every spot?

594
00:47:48,801 --> 00:47:52,434
- Then why didn't you answer?
- I was at a team dinner!

595
00:47:54,339 --> 00:47:56,789
You couldn't pick up while eating?

596
00:47:56,789 --> 00:47:58,797
What?

597
00:47:59,420 --> 00:48:00,717
Right.

598
00:48:00,717 --> 00:48:04,747
You're always stuck at home.
How would you understand work life?

599
00:48:04,747 --> 00:48:08,508
This is so frustrating.

600
00:48:15,387 --> 00:48:19,204
<i>If you don't want to stay at the bottom,</i>

601
00:48:19,204 --> 00:48:22,492
<i>you have to fight and win.</i>

602
00:48:47,851 --> 00:48:51,194
<i>In the end, holding your rank means</i>

603
00:48:51,194 --> 00:48:54,827
<i>surviving.</i>

604
00:49:00,780 --> 00:49:02,057
Huh?

605
00:49:02,057 --> 00:49:05,374
Why is he eliminated?

606
00:49:05,374 --> 00:49:09,791
He can sing, dance, he's good-looking,
he's got everything.

607
00:49:09,791 --> 00:49:13,248
He's clearly an ace. Why is he out?

608
00:49:13,248 --> 00:49:14,911
Why?

609
00:49:14,911 --> 00:49:17,434
Why?

610
00:49:58,487 --> 00:50:01,514
Ki Jun,

611
00:50:01,514 --> 00:50:04,231
she has a tip for Audit.

612
00:50:04,231 --> 00:50:07,747
She's been waiting since morning.

613
00:50:11,237 --> 00:50:13,641
I think my husband

614
00:50:13,641 --> 00:50:16,291
is having an affair.

615
00:50:16,291 --> 00:50:18,235
Oh my.

616
00:50:18,235 --> 00:50:20,568
When he came home

617
00:50:20,568 --> 00:50:24,958
with perfume as a birthday gift, I just knew.

618
00:50:24,958 --> 00:50:27,824
Perfume?

619
00:50:28,644 --> 00:50:33,315
Who gives perfume to a married man?
What else could it mean?

620
00:50:33,315 --> 00:50:37,345
It's marking territory by scent.

621
00:50:37,345 --> 00:50:41,155
Putting her scent on my man.

622
00:50:41,155 --> 00:50:43,439
After that, I watched him closely.

623
00:50:43,439 --> 00:50:45,816
He never puts his phone down.

624
00:50:45,816 --> 00:50:51,396
He even takes it into the shower.
I read online that means he's cheating.

625
00:50:52,420 --> 00:50:54,577
They're always glued together.

626
00:50:54,577 --> 00:50:58,747
They even travel for work together.
They text late at night.

627
00:50:58,747 --> 00:51:02,333
And I have proof.

628
00:51:13,212 --> 00:51:16,418
That's a hair.

629
00:51:17,021 --> 00:51:20,425
It was on his clothes. It has to be hers.

630
00:51:20,425 --> 00:51:23,338
I'm sure of it.

631
00:51:23,985 --> 00:51:26,090
Ma'am, this isn't really...

632
00:51:26,090 --> 00:51:30,199
We'll look into it and get back to you soon.

633
00:51:30,199 --> 00:51:32,912
Okay.

634
00:51:35,723 --> 00:51:37,509
What?

635
00:51:37,509 --> 00:51:39,932
<i>We got a tip, we follow procedure.</i>

636
00:51:39,932 --> 00:51:43,624
<i>Write a report, interview the parties.</i>

637
00:51:43,624 --> 00:51:47,410
<i>Go check it out. Now.</i>

638
00:51:48,659 --> 00:51:50,776
Check what?

639
00:51:50,776 --> 00:51:54,837
Run a DNA test on a hair?

640
00:51:54,837 --> 00:51:57,870
Beats me.

641
00:52:03,462 --> 00:52:04,998
Oh right,

642
00:52:04,998 --> 00:52:08,378
the Deputy Manager Son's wife was
scary yesterday, huh?

643
00:52:08,378 --> 00:52:11,002
She showed up because he wouldn't answer.

644
00:52:11,002 --> 00:52:13,471
She thinks he's involved
with Deputy Manager Jung.

645
00:52:13,471 --> 00:52:16,988
That's rough for her. She works nonstop.

646
00:52:16,988 --> 00:52:20,000
I kind of get it, though.

647
00:52:20,000 --> 00:52:23,047
Couples barely see each other at night.

648
00:52:23,047 --> 00:52:25,705
But coworkers are together all day.

649
00:52:25,705 --> 00:52:30,201
More in common, more to talk about.

650
00:52:30,201 --> 00:52:33,078
It gets to you.

651
00:52:33,078 --> 00:52:34,538
I wouldn't like it either.

652
00:52:34,538 --> 00:52:39,431
Still, there's a limit.
She's basically paranoid.

653
00:52:42,379 --> 00:52:44,850
She's famous.

654
00:52:44,850 --> 00:52:46,814
[Food Brand Planning Team]

655
00:52:46,814 --> 00:52:49,193
If we go like this,
Executive Kang will tear us apart.

656
00:52:49,193 --> 00:52:52,517
This is exactly what we agreed on.
Why does it keep changing?

657
00:52:52,517 --> 00:52:55,014
There's no clear focus.

658
00:52:55,014 --> 00:52:57,667
It's not about local competitors.

659
00:52:57,667 --> 00:53:00,391
I told you,
we need to focus on global expansion.

660
00:53:00,391 --> 00:53:03,620
<i>They're just coworkers. Not an affair.</i>

661
00:53:03,620 --> 00:53:06,282
- Huh?
- You don't remember?

662
00:53:08,079 --> 00:53:10,749
Let's analyze all companies under 1 billion.

663
00:53:10,749 --> 00:53:13,121
- We need everything.
- Got it.

664
00:53:13,121 --> 00:53:16,273
But how many registrations...

665
00:53:16,273 --> 00:53:18,759
Well... yeah.

666
00:53:21,623 --> 00:53:25,316
Hey! Over here!

667
00:53:30,033 --> 00:53:32,899
- Alright, everyone's here?
- Yes.

668
00:53:32,899 --> 00:53:36,622
We've got a major task.

669
00:53:36,622 --> 00:53:38,553
Straight from the top.

670
00:53:38,553 --> 00:53:40,279
From the top?

671
00:53:40,279 --> 00:53:43,976
So drop everything and handle this first.

672
00:53:43,976 --> 00:53:46,166
There's a criminal angle,

673
00:53:46,166 --> 00:53:49,264
and if it gets out, it'll blow up in the press.

674
00:53:49,264 --> 00:53:54,170
So we handle it quietly, clean and discreet.

675
00:53:54,170 --> 00:53:56,503
Got it?

676
00:53:56,503 --> 00:53:57,994
What is it?

677
00:53:57,994 --> 00:54:00,794
[Audit on site]
[Thank you for your cooperation]

678
00:54:01,861 --> 00:54:03,699
So, there are poppies here?

679
00:54:03,699 --> 00:54:07,277
Hey, keep your voice down.

680
00:54:07,277 --> 00:54:11,116
The security guard found one
while clearing the flower bed.

681
00:54:11,116 --> 00:54:13,122
Not the decorative kind.

682
00:54:13,122 --> 00:54:15,617
There might be more planted,

683
00:54:15,617 --> 00:54:17,987
so we handle it quietly
before it becomes an issue.

684
00:54:17,987 --> 00:54:20,371
Got it?

685
00:54:20,371 --> 00:54:24,522
A pharma company with poppies...

686
00:54:24,522 --> 00:54:26,776
Hey, did you eat one?

687
00:54:26,776 --> 00:54:28,923
Don't go picking random stuff
just because it's free.

688
00:54:28,923 --> 00:54:32,085
Come on, just find them already.

689
00:54:39,158 --> 00:54:40,190
Hello?

690
00:54:40,190 --> 00:54:44,900
<i>I'm Deputy Manager Son's wife.
Did you check? The hair?</i>

691
00:54:44,900 --> 00:54:46,924
We'll send the results by email.

692
00:54:46,924 --> 00:54:50,557
I'm in the middle of something,
so I'll hang up.

693
00:55:02,624 --> 00:55:05,018
Yes?

694
00:55:05,018 --> 00:55:08,175
<i>You said you'd call right away.</i>

695
00:55:08,175 --> 00:55:11,720
<i>It's Deputy Manager Jung, right?</i>

696
00:55:12,958 --> 00:55:15,649
<i>So what happens to them now?</i>

697
00:55:15,649 --> 00:55:17,614
<i>The company should handle this strictly...</i>

698
00:55:17,614 --> 00:55:21,131
Enough already!

699
00:55:21,131 --> 00:55:23,489
There's nothing going on.

700
00:55:23,489 --> 00:55:25,880
They're just working.

701
00:55:25,880 --> 00:55:28,599
<i>They're together right now?</i>

702
00:55:28,599 --> 00:55:29,883
<i>Did you see them?</i>

703
00:55:29,883 --> 00:55:34,442
Ma'am, don't do this.

704
00:55:34,442 --> 00:55:40,045
You should see a doctor. This is paranoia!

705
00:55:53,213 --> 00:55:55,959
You've got crap on you.

706
00:56:03,976 --> 00:56:05,910
Gosh.

707
00:56:14,622 --> 00:56:16,223
Rehearsal's in the main conference room, huh?

708
00:56:16,223 --> 00:56:18,227
Yeah. I told the team we're heading in.

709
00:56:18,227 --> 00:56:20,567
Hold on.

710
00:56:26,506 --> 00:56:28,819
Thanks.

711
00:57:15,044 --> 00:57:17,795
At least you bloom,

712
00:57:17,795 --> 00:57:20,714
in this dull office.

713
00:57:42,283 --> 00:57:45,689
Oh, Ki Jun. Heading out?

714
00:57:48,894 --> 00:57:51,991
I read your report on Son Myeong Su.

715
00:57:51,991 --> 00:57:53,631
That's really all?

716
00:57:53,631 --> 00:57:56,475
You're sure there's no affair?

717
00:57:56,475 --> 00:57:58,315
No.

718
00:57:58,315 --> 00:58:00,632
I can't be certain about something
between two people.

719
00:58:00,632 --> 00:58:02,509
There's no solid evidence.

720
00:58:02,509 --> 00:58:06,002
Based on what we checked,
there's nothing there.

721
00:58:07,492 --> 00:58:09,806
I like that you don't jump to conclusions.

722
00:58:09,806 --> 00:58:14,619
But since it's between two people,
shouldn't we dig a little deeper?

723
00:58:16,271 --> 00:58:18,015
- Hello.
- Hello.

724
00:58:18,015 --> 00:58:20,102
- Oh, Food Brand Team, right?
- Yes.

725
00:58:20,102 --> 00:58:24,595
- Working late? Hang in there.
- Hello.

726
00:58:25,667 --> 00:58:28,617
Where are Deputy Manager Son and Jung?

727
00:58:28,617 --> 00:58:31,797
They're prepping for a PT.
We're grabbing dinner.

728
00:58:31,797 --> 00:58:33,858
I see.

729
00:58:33,858 --> 00:58:38,495
How do you know all of us?
You really are "God Joo."

730
00:58:38,495 --> 00:58:39,527
"God Joo?"

731
00:58:39,527 --> 00:58:42,721
You see everything and know everything.

732
00:58:42,721 --> 00:58:45,998
Is that what they say? No way.

733
00:58:45,998 --> 00:58:48,042
"God Joo?"

734
00:58:48,042 --> 00:58:51,341
I know your team's working
on something important.

735
00:58:51,341 --> 00:58:52,392
Alright.

736
00:58:52,392 --> 00:58:55,145
You've been working late,
so God Joo's treating tonight.

737
00:58:55,145 --> 00:58:57,562
Something nice and expensive.

738
00:58:57,562 --> 00:59:00,515
You're amazing! God Joo!

739
00:59:00,515 --> 00:59:04,425
I'll send it up for everyone.
Head back upstairs.

740
00:59:04,425 --> 00:59:07,918
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

741
00:59:12,195 --> 00:59:16,453
- Keep it up.
- Thank you.

742
00:59:20,244 --> 00:59:23,223
- You should rewrite the report.
- What?

743
00:59:23,223 --> 00:59:27,565
Maybe I really am God Joo. Nice nickname.

744
00:59:33,887 --> 00:59:37,091
Want to run it again?

745
00:59:37,091 --> 00:59:39,791
Yes, sir.

746
00:59:43,502 --> 00:59:45,895
But...

747
00:59:50,531 --> 00:59:52,830
run what?

748
00:59:58,107 --> 01:00:00,761
This?

749
01:00:20,626 --> 01:00:23,656
What do you mean? Rewrite the report?

750
01:00:23,656 --> 01:00:25,493
You'll find out tomorrow.

751
01:00:25,493 --> 01:00:28,899
Or maybe... tonight.

752
01:01:15,195 --> 01:01:17,452
Are you okay?

753
01:01:17,452 --> 01:01:20,425
What about you?

754
01:01:20,425 --> 01:01:23,278
What the...

755
01:01:43,209 --> 01:01:45,636
Ma'am?

756
01:01:58,391 --> 01:02:00,051
What?

757
01:02:00,051 --> 01:02:02,650
Paranoid?

758
01:02:04,827 --> 01:02:07,704
Why is everyone coming at me?

759
01:02:07,704 --> 01:02:11,817
I'm not the crazy one. They are!

760
01:02:15,872 --> 01:02:18,535
I'll kill them!

761
01:03:29,072 --> 01:03:31,310
<i>He's the pride of our team.</i>

762
01:03:31,310 --> 01:03:33,287
<i>Oh, you're the team's pride.</i>

763
01:03:33,287 --> 01:03:34,588
<i>Why is she being so shameless?</i>

764
01:03:34,588 --> 01:03:39,923
<i>If everyone were like you,
this place would be a lot better.</i>

765
01:03:39,923 --> 01:03:43,010
<i>Don't be an idiot.</i>

766
01:03:43,010 --> 01:03:44,693
<i>Get the job done right this time.</i>

767
01:03:44,693 --> 01:03:47,966
<i>Basement Level 4, Section F.</i>

768
01:03:47,966 --> 01:03:49,897
<i>- We need to catch them.
- Catch them?</i>

769
01:03:49,897 --> 01:03:51,403
<i>How do we even catch that?</i>

770
01:03:51,403 --> 01:03:54,487
<i>Ethics? Are you a cop or a judge?</i>

771
01:03:54,487 --> 01:03:56,445
<i>You hate Joo In Ah that much?</i>

772
01:03:56,445 --> 01:03:57,896
<i>Should I just quit?</i>

773
01:03:57,896 --> 01:04:00,945
<i>If you want out of Audit,
you should've said so.</i>

774
01:04:00,945 --> 01:04:04,094
<i>Instead of talking behind my back.</i>

